---
description: Bump web/api package version on significant changes; CI uses web/api versions for tags.
alwaysApply: true
---

When doing significant changes in the web package, bump `version` in `web/package.json` according to semantic versioning.

When doing significant changes in the api package, bump `version` in `api/package.json` according to semantic versioning.

Root `package.json` version is not used for release image tags in CI; release tags are derived from `web/package.json` and `api/package.json`.

On `main` pushes, CI reads `web/package.json` and `api/package.json` versions and publishes image tags including `v<version>`, `latest`, and `sha-<short_sha>` per component (see `.github/workflows/build-and-push.yml`).

On `dev` pushes, CI publishes `<component>-dev-<full_commit_sha>` and `<component>-dev-latest` tags (e.g. `web-dev-ŌĆ”`, `api-dev-ŌĆ”`); semver `v*` tags are not used for dev builds.

`libs/shared-types/package.json` also has an independent `version` field (`@meriter/shared-types`).